Appeals for good behaviour were very necessary in the case of the miscellaneous throng which composed the audience in a Roman theatre, as in the Poenulus of Plautus, where nurses are requested not to bring in babies, ‘ne et ipsae sitiant, et pueri pereant same ; neve esurientes hic quasi haedi obvagz·ant.’ grex, ‘the troupe3’ dux gregis, ‘the manager,' who was also the chief actor, in this case Turpio, and so called in v. 33 actor.
